The app uses Solid’s technology so that users can create their own personal online data storage or a POD.
It can include contact lists, task lists, a calendar, a music library and other private and corporate tools.
Similar to Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify, all contents are available in one browser and at the same time.
The particular thing about the personal online data storage is that the user alone can decide who can access which data.
The company refers to this concept as personal strengthening and development on data.
According to CEO John Bruce, the idea behind Inrupt is that the company uses resources, processes, and appropriate skills to make Solid available for everyone.
